# ER Diagram to Relational Schema Transformation

The Synapse Fest Database was initially modeled using an Entity-Relationship (ER) diagram representing 
the major entities, attributes, and relationships involved in managing a college festival. 
The ER diagram was then transformed into a relational schema by applying standard ER-to-Relational mapping rules.

The objective was to convert conceptual entities and relationships into relations that can be implemented in PostgreSQL 
while preserving data integrity and minimizing redundancy.

### Mapping Rules

1. Every strong entity was converted into a relation with its primary key.

2. Multivalued attributes such as phone numbers were separated into independent relations.

3. One-to-Many (1:N) relationships were implemented using foreign keys on the many side.

4. Many-to-Many (M:N) relationships were converted into associative relations containing the primary keys of participating entities.

5. Derived attributes were not stored and were computed whenever required.

6. Integrity constraints were later enforced through primary keys, foreign keys, CHECK constraints, and triggers.

##Several entities contained multivalued phone numbers in the ER model. To maintain First Normal Form (1NF), separate relations were created.

Examples:

COMMITTEE_PHONE(comm_id, phone)

ATTENDEE_PHONE(attendee_id, phone)

ARTIST_PHONE(artist_id, phone)

JUDGES_PHONE(judge_id, phone)

VOLUNTEER_PHONE(volunteer_id, phone)

SPONSOR_PHONE(sponsor_id, phone)

VENDOR_PHONE(vendor_id, phone)

Each relation uses a composite primary key consisting of the owner identifier and phone number.

## Relationship Mapping

One-to-Many Relationships

| Relationship                              | Implementation        |
| ----------------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| Committee manages Event                   | EVENT.comm_id         |
| Venue hosts Event                         | EVENT.venue_id        |
| Venue contains Vendor                     | VENDOR.venue_id       |
| Venue associated with Lost & Found report | LOST_FOUND.venue_id   |
| Attendee purchases Ticket                 | TICKET.attendee_id    |
| Ticket belongs to Ticket Type             | TICKET.ticket_type_id |


Many-to-Many Relationships

| Relationship                 | Relation                   |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Event – Judge                | EVENT_JUDGES               |
| Event – Artist               | EVENT_ARTIST               |
| Ticket Type – Event          | TICKET_TYPE_EVENT          |
| Committee – Sponsor          | COMMITTEE_SPONSOR          |
| Committee – Volunteer        | COMMITTEE_VOLUNTEER        |
| Committee – Committee Member | COMMITTEE_COMMITTEE_MEMBER |
| Venue – Facility             | VENUE_FACILITY             |




